### **5. Detailed Statistical Analysis**

#### 5.1. Overall Dimensional Scores

The scores reveal a wide variance in constitutional rhetoric across the corpus. Institutionalist speeches (McCain, Romney) score high on health dimensions, while Populist and Civil Rights speeches show high pathology.

| Speaker | Era | Ideology | Proc. Health | Inst. Health | Sys. Health | **CDI** |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :---: | :---: | :---: | :---: |
| John McCain | Institutional | Conservative | 1.00 | 0.90 | 0.90 | **0.93** |
| Mitt Romney | Institutional | Conservative | 0.90 | 0.10 | 0.80 | **0.60** |
| Cory Booker | Institutional | Progressive | 0.75 | 0.05 | 0.75 | **0.52** |
| Steve King | Populist | Conservative | 0.70 | -0.70 | 0.80 | **0.27** |
| J.D. Vance | Populist | Conservative | -0.60 | -0.80 | 0.40 | **-0.33** |
| Bernie Sanders | Populist | Progressive | 0.05 | -0.70 | -0.50 | **-0.38** |
| A. Ocasio-Cortez | Populist | Progressive | -0.30 | -0.75 | -0.65 | **-0.57** |
| John Lewis | Civil Rights | Progressive | -0.60 | -0.70 | -0.75 | **-0.68** |

